The paper deals with the problem of identifying a subset of non-defective items from a large population using group testing. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT) as it involves analyzing the probability of error and obtaining bounds on the number of tests required. The algorithms presented in the paper are computationally efficient and analytically tractable, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithms in practical scenarios, which may make it relevant to the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
